casebody.data:
ADAMS against SCULL.

ON CERTIORARI.

The action below was brought for twelve penalties, under the timber act. The matter was submitted to referees; the referees reported in favor of the plaintiff below, $15.80 debt, and $6.40 costs. Sundry errors were assigned, but the court took notice of one only, to wit, that no specific penalty was awarded, but fractional parts of two penalties. No judgment being rendered, the court declared the proceedings

Null and void.
